b'Caused by the grand asynchronous movement of 2014.  Specifically, the asynchronous code in the comm that calls back the user registered message handling function.

The output assumes (now incorrectly) that the widget custom messages are received by the front-end in the same order as the stdout/display messages. 

@takluyver @jasongrout :horse: '

b'Hey all --

I'm noticing that setting the state of a `Unicode` member of a `widgets.DOMWidget` triggers the JS `update` method twice. I found this thread from the mailing list: http://mail.scipy.org/pipermail/ipython-dev/2014-February/013277.html

Here is an illustration:
![Changing IPython state triggers update twice](http://i.imgur.com/FoULrva.gif)

Here is the code:

```javascript
%%javascript
require(["widgets/js/widget"], function(WidgetManager){
    
    var HelloView = IPython.DOMWidgetView.extend({
        
        render: function(){ 
            this.value_changed();
            this.model.on('change:value', this.value_changed, this);
        },
        
        update: function() {
            alert(this.model.get('value')); 
            console.log(this.model.get('value'));
            
            return GraphView.__super__.update.apply(this);
        }
    });
    
    // manager.WidgetManager.register_widget_view('HelloView', HelloView);
    WidgetManager.register_widget_view('HelloView', HelloView);
});

//@ sourceURL=BasicWidget.js
```

```python
from IPython.html import widgets
from IPython.utils.traitlets import Unicode


class HelloWidget(widgets.DOMWidget):
    _view_name = Unicode('HelloView', sync=True)
    value = Unicode('Hello World!', sync=True)


w = HelloWidget()

w.value = 'asdf'
````

Is this intended, fixed, already noted, etc? Are there any workarounds? I can assign a unique ID the messages that I'm sending and filter them in JS land, but I'd rather not send the messages twice, as they can be pretty big sometimes!

Thanks! '

